toWatch.title: Aliens Abducted My Parents and Now I Feel Kinda Left Out

movies.title: Star Trek: Section 31
movies.thoughts: I enjoyed this as a sci-fi action movie, but feel it missed the mark as a Star Trek movie. Even still, Michelle Yeoh did a fantastic job as Georgiou.

movies.title: Despicable Me 2
movies.thoughts: Cute and enjoyable. A little predictable, but glad we watched it.

movies.title: Wargames
movies.thoughts: This was definitely an 80s movie, but still enjoyable.

movies.title: Despicable Me
movies.thoughts: Cute and enjoyable

movies.title: Indiana Jones and the Temple of Doom
movies.thoughts: Definitely liked Raiders of the Lost Ark better. Not sure if it’s time or what, but this felt kind of corny.

movies.title: The Man from Toronto
movies.thoughts: This was about as dumb as I expected it to be. Mostly predictable, but still enjoyable.

movies.title: The Dead Don’t Die
movies.thoughts: What a strange movie.

movies.title: Office Christmas Party
movies.thoughts: This movie was predictable and dumb, but it was funny and enjoyable.

movies.title: American Gangster
movies.thoughts: It was an enjoyable movie. Good characters and a good plot. Felt a little dragged out at times though.

movies.title: Dune: Part One
movies.thoughts: The visuals were amazing for this. The story I believe does the book justice and the casting is fantastic.

movies.title: Clue
movies.thoughts: This was enjoyable. Got a bunch of good laughs and had a pretty good cast.

movies.title: Apollo 13 Survival
movies.thoughts: I thought it was an interesting documentary. I'm still kind of surprised they didn't really talk about the cause of the disaster any though.

movies.title: The Holdovers
movies.thoughts: I enjoyed it. I liked the characters and while the story was somewhat predictable, it was still a good watch.

movies.title: Won’t You Be My Neighbor
movies.thoughts: This was as interesting look back at Mr. Rogers and while not as in-depth as I had anticipated, it was nostalgic and showed how amazing Fred Rogers really was.

movies.title: Identity Thief
movies.thoughts: It was dumb, but still enjoyable.

movies.title: The Accountant
movies.thoughts: There were some decent action scenes, but some characters and roles seemed kind of superfluous, like the movie would have been just fine without them.

movies.title: Being the Ricardos
movies.thoughts: This ended up being something completely different than what I anticipated, but not in a bad way. It just showed a different side of the show than I expected.

movies.title: Sicario
movies.thoughts: I thought this would be better given the cast. In the end, I felt like several of the characters were superfluous and the story disjointed.

movies.title: Asteroid City
movies.thoughts: This was just weird. I guess I’m not really surprised since it’s a Wes Anderson film, but I really don’t know what to make of it.

movies.title: The Many Saints of Newark
movies.thoughts: Not really sure I liked it…felt disjointed and with some storylines just never finished or flushed out.

movies.title: The Foreigner
movies.thoughts: This wasn’t quite what I expected. It was still a decent action flick with some intrigue.

movies.title: Anyone But You
movies.thoughts: This was a typical romantic comedy. It was mostly predictable but still enjoyable.

movies.title: Patriot Games
movies.thoughts: A Clancy film with Harrison Ford as Jack Ryan. Definitely shows its age and might be slightly predictable, but still enjoyable.

movies.title: Ghostbusters: Frozen Empire
movies.thoughts: This was slightly predictable, but still an enjoyable follow-up to Afterlife.

movies.title: Ghostbusters: Afterlife
movies.thoughts: I really enjoyed this. I thought they did a good job of telling a new story while still paying homage to the past.

movies.title: The Hateful Eight
movies.thoughts: This was definitely a Tarantino movie. I thought the story was somewhat predictable, but was still enjoyable.

movies.title: John Wick
movies.thoughts: A pretty prototypical action flick. Still enjoyable.

movies.title: My Cousin Vinny
movies.thoughts: This had some good points, not sure why it’s considered such a classic though.

movies.title: Dark Shadows
movies.thoughts: This was strange. Not awful, but strange.

movies.title: Heat
movies.thoughts: De Niro vs. Pacino. They don’t make heist movies like this anymore.

movies.title: This is the End
movies.thoughts: I didn’t go into this with high expectations. I was not disappointed, dumb, but did have its moments.

movies.title: Once Upon a Time in Hollywood
movies.thoughts: I found the movie to be dragged out far longer than it needed to be.

movies.title: Quiz Lady
movies.thoughts: A somewhat predictable comedy, but still enjoyable with some good laughs.

movies.title: Alien: Resurrection
movies.thoughts: It was okay. Definitely felt like the series was drawn out 1 sequel too many.

movies.title: The Menu
movies.thoughts: Another weird one. I’m really not sure how I feel about it.

movies.title: Snowpiercer
movies.thoughts: This movie was kind of weird for my tastes. Some good action scenes, but the ending seemed a little lackluster.

movies.title: U-571
movies.thoughts: This was a typical war movie that was enjoyable, albeit  a little predictable.

movies.title: Father Christmas is Back
movies.thoughts: Had some good humor to it with your typical Christmas tropes. Somewhat predictable but still watchable.

movies.title: Alien3
movies.thoughts: I think I liked the first 2 movies better, but this was still an enjoyable sci-fi thriller. The ending was a little too predictable.

movies.title: A Haunting in Venice
movies.thoughts: Always love a good mystery movie.

movies.title: Interstellar
movies.thoughts: The visuals for the movie were phenomenal. The story was solid and was interesting.

movies.title: Aliens
movies.thoughts: I enjoyed this one. It holds up well enough too after over 30 years.

movies.title: BlackBerry
movies.thoughts: I thought this was ok. Glenn Howerton reminded me of his Dennis character from Sunny.

movies.title: Star Trek: Nemesis
movies.thoughts: I know this movie gets a bad rap and it does have its issues, but I still enjoy it. Last time seeing the Enterprise E in action.

movies.title: Young Frankenstein
movies.thoughts: I know this is considered a classic, but I can’t say I liked it all that much. It had its lines, but I’m a “meh” at best on it.

movies.title: Mad Max: Fury Road
movies.thoughts: Maybe I’m not the target audience but I found this movie to be weird and incredibly predictable.

movies.title: Oppenheimer
movies.thoughts: I enjoyed this. I’m not 100% sure how much was dramatized, but it provided a good look at both the interest in the science and the post-WWII realization of what they did.

movies.title: Bull Durham
movies.thoughts: Typical ‘80s movie, but enjoyable. Some good bits of humor and baseball.

movies.title: Alien
movies.thoughts: Even 40 years later the sci fi & horror aspects hold up. The movie was and is fantastic!

movies.title: Bros
movies.thoughts: This was a typical romantic comedy. It had some good scenes and a positive message.

movies.title: Barbie
movies.thoughts: I enjoyed this. It had a good mix of humor with a positive message.

movies.title: Star Trek: Beyond
movies.thoughts: I’m not entirely sure I enjoyed this as much of the others, but it was definitely Star Trek and a good Trek action film.

movies.title: Star Trek: Into Darkness
movies.thoughts: I know there’s a bunch of hate over the Khan reveal, but I actually enjoyed this movie. It even brings in some of the moral commentary Star Trek is known for.

movies.title: Star Trek
movies.thoughts: I enjoyed the reintroduction to the Star Trek series. The replacements for Kirk & crew do a great job reprising the roles and there’s a good mix of humor and action.

movies.title: For the Love of Spock
movies.thoughts: This was a nice look back into Leonard Nimoy and what he brought to Star Trek and science fiction in general. It was through the eyes of his son Adam and had actors from all walks of Trek and other shows on it. It wasn’t afraid to talk about the more-grim side either.

movies.title: The Out-Laws
movies.thoughts: This was particularly dumb, but it still had some good humor. It wasn’t the best movie ever, but I enjoyed it.

movies.title: Dungeons & Dragons: Among Thieves
movies.thoughts: I enjoyed this movie. It was a good fantasy flick with a good mix of humor. Chris Pine was funny, Michelle Rodriguez brought the action and the supporting cast were likeable.

movies.title: Charlie Wilson’s War
movies.thoughts: I’m not entirely sure what I was expecting when I started this. It wasn’t a bad movie and Tom Hanks did a great job, it just felt kinda “meh”.

movies.title: Inside Man
movies.thoughts: I enjoyed this with its twists and turns.

movies.title: The Gray Man
movies.thoughts: This was definitely a good action flick. Ryan Gosling and Chris Evans both did a great job.

movies.title: The Shawshank Redemption
movies.thoughts: I don’t know if I ever saw this all the way through, but the movie was fantastic. Tim Robbins & Morgan Freeman were great in it.

movies.title: Gatsby
movies.thoughts: Some things I remembered from the book…some things I didn’t. I didn’t hate the adaptation.

movies.title: Raiders of the Lost Ark
movies.thoughts: 40 some years later, this still holds up.

movies.title: This is Where I Leave You
movies.thoughts: Wasn’t a bad movie. It had a good mix of humor and drama. It was a little predictable though.

movies.title: Sorry to Bother You
movies.thoughts: This movie started off good…then jumped the shark.

movies.title: Margin Call
movies.thoughts: I’m not sure how to feel about this other than it feels very much like Wall Street.

movies.title: Death on the Nile
movies.thoughts: Had some nice twist and turns. While the ending made sense, not entirely sure how we got there.

movies.title: The Harder they Fall
movies.thoughts: I enjoyed the movie. It had good action sequences and the cast was fantastic.

movies.title: You People
movies.thoughts: Had a lot of good laughs from this. Jonah Hill and Lauren London had good performances.

movies.title: Clerks
movies.thoughts: The movie was not as good as I remember it being.

movies.title: The Irishman
movies.thoughts: I’m not sure what the hype was around this. De Niro, Pesci & Pacino were good, but the movie dragged on way too long.

movies.title: Amsterdam
movies.thoughts: This was a weird movie. Felt kind of weird given the way the story was told versus the true parts of the story

movies.title: Jurassic World: Dominon
movies.thoughts: Definitely glad I didn’t see this in the theaters. Nothing compares to the first Jurassic Park movie.

movies.title: Glass Onion
movies.thoughts: This had a good cast and Daniel Craig was fantastic. Definitely some good twists.

movies.title: Elysium
movies.thoughts: It wasn’t quite as good as I expected and kind of predictable, but I still enjoyed it.

movies.title: Star Trek: Generations
movies.thoughts: I feel like this is an underrated Trek film. Outside of an annoying plot hole (that I see), it’s actually a solid Star Trek movie.

movies.title: National Lampoon’s Christmas Vacation
movies.thoughts: Definitely by far my favorite Christmas Movie. Great cast with plenty of good jokes.

movies.title: Whiskey Tango Foxtrot
movies.thoughts: Tina Fey did a good job in her role here. Ending wasn’t quite as satisfying as I was hoping for but it was still good.

movies.title: A Christmas Story
movies.thoughts: Finally saw this classic Christmas movie all the way through. I know it might be sacrilege, but my thoughts were “meh”

movies.title: Free Guy
movies.thoughts: It was a good mix of dumb and fun, I really enjoyed it.

movies.title: Don’t Worry, Darling
movies.thoughts: This movie was creepy.

movies.title: Uncharted
movies.thoughts: I didn’t hate this. I don’t want to give much away, but they didn’t do a horrible job of adapting the characters.

movies.title: The Munsters (2022)
movies.thoughts: Was dumb...but not necessarily in a bad way

movies.title: Clear and Present Danger
movies.thoughts: It's been a while since I had seen this, and even longer since I had read the book. It wasn't bad, but I'm not sure how well it's held up.

movies.title: Vengeance
movies.thoughts: Some of it was predictable, other parts weren't. Didn't draw me in as much as I'd hoped but was still worth watching.

movies.title: Star Trek: Insurrection
movies.thoughts: I know this isn't one of the favorites of most Trekkies, but I actually really enjoyed it. It does feel a bit like a 2 part episode but that's certainly not a bad thing.

movies.title: Star Trek: First Contact
movies.thoughts: Arguably the best Star Trek TNG movie. Brings in philosophy with a nice mix of horror and action. Patrick Stewart was fantastic.

movies.title: The Bob’s Burgers Movie
movies.thoughts: It was your typical Bob's Burgers episode...only movie length. I did enjoy it.
I had been meaning to watch this for a long time. I enjoyed it tremendously. Chadwick Boseman does a fantastic job as Jackie Robinson

movies.title: Don’t Look Up
movies.thoughts: I think the scariest part of this movie was how much I could totally see this happen today given the state of politics in America.

movies.title: No Time to Die
movies.thoughts: Some good action scenes, but the main villain didn’t make much sense to me which definitely put the movie on a down note.

movies.title: Scrooged
movies.thoughts: Was an enjoyable twist on Charles Dickens’

movies.title: Ghostbusters: Afterlife
movies.thoughts: I really enjoyed this. I thought they did a good job of telling a new story while still paying homage to the past.

movies.title: Mars Attacks
movies.thoughts: A dumb but funny movie with a great cast.

movies.title: Muppets Haunted Mansion
movies.thoughts: This was basically what I expected.

movies.title: Spectre
movies.thoughts: Not one of Craig's best Bond films, but still a good Bond film nonetheless.

movies.title: War Machine
movies.thoughts: Not sure how I feel about it. Somehow, despite it being satire, it felt rather accurate to what happened in Afghanistan.

movies.title: The Hunt for Red October
movies.thoughts: I've generally enjoyed Tom Clancy novels, and this movie was done well. Connery & Baldwin do a great job.

movies.title: Breach
movies.thoughts: I had only heard of Robert Hanssen, while dramatized, this did fill in some of the gaps. Great acting by Cooper and Ryan Phillipe.

movies.title: The Highwaymen
movies.thoughts: I enjoyed this telling of the end of Bonnie & Clyde. Costner & Harrelson did a fantastic job.

movies.title: The Departed
movies.thoughts: This had been on my list to watch for a while. It was a good movie, but I guess I didn't feel like the ending was as satisfying as I hoped it would be.

movies.title: Gordon Lightfoot: If You Could Read My Mind
movies.thoughts: My Dad often listened to Gordon Lightfoot while I was growing up, so needless to say, I've grown an appreciation for his music. This was an interesting documentary about his life and history with folk music.

movies.title: Moneyball
movies.thoughts: As a baseball fan, and a fan of Michael Lewis' writing, I loved the story of how baseball has probably seen its biggest change in the last 50 years with how teams are built and players evaluated.

movies.title: 9to5: The Story of a Movement
movies.thoughts: I always knew that women have had it tough in the workplace. This documentary gave me a much better understanding of the fight they've undertaken.

movies.title: The Current War
movies.thoughts: I went into this thinking this was an Edison vs. Tesla movie and was pleasantly surprised that it was far more than that.

movies.title: Sherlock Holmes
movies.thoughts: Wasn’t a horrible adaptation of Sherlock Holmes, but I still prefer Sherlock & Elementary.

movies.title: Hotel Artemis
movies.thoughts: I'm still not sure how I feel about the movie, but it has a fantastic cast.

movies.title: Star Trek VI: The Undiscovered Country
movies.thoughts: This is my second favorite original Trek movie. Coming out right around the end of the Cold War, this does a good job relating to that time in history.

movies.title: Skyfall
movies.thoughts: Definitely my favorite Daniel Craig Bond film. The interaction between Judi Dench as 'M' and Craig really shines here.

movies.title: Star Trek V: The Final Frontier
movies.thoughts: As much as I love Star Trek, the only redeeming part of this movie is probably Kirk's "What does God need with a starship?" line

movies.title: Capital in the 21st Century
movies.thoughts: Informative and disheartening at the same time. This documentary does a good job of looking back at what led to the current economic inequality and the rigged system.

movies.title: Star Trek IV: The Voyage Home
movies.thoughts: Star Trek & time travel...often a fun mix.

movies.title: Star Trek III: The Search for Spock
movies.thoughts: Being an odd-numbered Trek film, this one often gets overlooked. It’s still one of my favorites.

movies.title: Star Trek II: The Wrath of Khan
movies.thoughts: The quintessential Star Trek film. Definitely one of the best, if not the best Trek film.

movies.title: Star Trek: The Motion Picture
movies.thoughts: Better than I remember it, but awfully slow.

movies.title: Quantum of Solace
movies.thoughts: Not one of the better Bond films. Still a decent action flick.

movies.title: The Game Changers
movies.thoughts: This was an interesting documentary about plant based diets. Part of me felt it was trying to sell me on the idea of going more plant based, but it does follow other things I’ve read. Worth a watch.

movies.title: The Prestige
movies.thoughts: The twists and turns of this movie were enjoyable. Christian Bale and Hugh Jackman did phenomenal jobs.

movies.title: Casino Royale
movies.thoughts: Daniel Craig does a fantastic job stepping into the role of 007 in this. The casting all around is fantastic.

movies.title: Die Another Day
movies.thoughts: Brosnan's final film as Bond is another good one.

movies.title: Tinker Tailor Soldier Spy
movies.thoughts: I really enjoyed the intrigue in this one. It did take me a little to pick out the characters though.

movies.title: Hail, Caesar!
movies.thoughts: This was definitely a Coen Brothers film. It was solid, not as funny as I expected, but still good.

movies.title: The Nice Guys
movies.thoughts: I enjoyed this one. Russell Crowe and Ryan Gosling play well off each other.

movies.title: The Death of Stalin
movies.thoughts: Can't say I really understood this one.

movies.title: The World is Not Enough
movies.thoughts: Definitely better than I remembered it. Still the weakest of the Brosnan Bond films.

movies.title: The Royal Tenenbaums
movies.thoughts: I wasn't a huge fan of this one. It had a few moments here and there, but overall I didn't really get it.

movies.title: Tomorrow Never Dies
movies.thoughts: Another good Bond film.

movies.title: Man of the Year
movies.thoughts: I seem to remember liking this movie a lot more when I first saw it. Still not bad.

movies.title: Goldeneye
movies.thoughts: Still one of the best Bond films out there. A great intro to Pierce Brosnan as 007.

abandoned.title: Saltburn
abandoned.thoughts: I tried to finish this, but I just couldn't. It was just getting too creepy for me, and not even a good creepy.
